              <ol>
                <li>
                  <b>Tank Water Heaters:</b>
                  <p>Tank water heaters are the traditional choice for many households, typically storing between 20 to 80 gallons of hot water that is readily available for use. These systems are generally reliable but can experience issues such as sediment buildup, which can affect efficiency and lead to leaks. Common repair needs include replacing the anode rod to prevent tank corrosion, fixing or replacing thermostats and heating elements, and addressing valve issues. Regular maintenance, including flushing the tank annually, can help mitigate many of these problems and extend the lifespan of your tank water heater.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Tankless Water Heaters:</b>
                  <p>Tankless water heaters, also known as on-demand water heaters, provide hot water only as needed, which makes them energy-efficient and space-saving. However, they have their own set of repair needs. Common issues include mineral buildup, which can restrict water flow and reduce efficiency, and problems with the ignition system or heating elements. Additionally, because these units have complex electronics, they occasionally require software updates or electrical component repairs. Regular descaling and professional inspections can help keep a tankless water heater in peak condition.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <b>Heat Pump Water Heaters:</b>
                  <p>Heat pump water heaters are highly efficient systems that use electricity to move heat from the air or ground to heat water. These units are generally more complex and may require specialized repairs. Common issues include problems with the evaporator coil, compressor, or refrigerant levels. Additionally, these systems may experience issues with the fan motor or electrical components. Given their complexity, itâ€™s crucial to have a certified technician perform regular maintenance and any necessary repairs to ensure efficient operation and longevity.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
